  "result": "Fix confirmed.\n\n**Root cause:** `crates/lua-vm/src/vm.rs:1146` — `fmodf` tested for \"operands have opposite signs\" via `r * n < 0.0`. With subnormal inputs (line 600/601 of `math.lua` operates on `b ≈ 1e-292`), the product `r * n` underflows to zero, so the sign-correction branch was skipped and Lua's floor-mod returned the wrong sign (e.g. `(-2.1*b) % (2*b)` yielded `-1e-293` instead of `1.9e-292`).\n\n**Fix:** Replaced the multiplication-based opposite-sign test with a direct sign comparison (`r > 0 ? n < 0 : r < 0 && n > 0`), matching C-Lua's `luai_nummod` macro exactly.\n\n**New state:** Inline reproduction now returns `1.9e-292` for `(-2.1*b) % (2*b)` as expected. The mega-loop will re-execute the full math.lua to confirm; I did not re-run the official test, only the targeted micro-repro.",
